        <mxCell id="tWbI7mr-YFgMqcFsaV5p-76" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="sqlite3" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="120" x="878.57" y="3920" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="tWbI7mr-YFgMqcFsaV5p-84" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;" value="&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description of the architecture:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The project is already given following the principles of a Front Controller design architecture,&amp;nbsp; where a class uses the rest of the other components (dashboard uses the rest of the views).&amp;nbsp; We can get to see different components: Employee, supplier, product, billing, sales and category.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A python file &quot;create database&quot; is run so that with sqlite3, there will be a database where the data of the application will be stored.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Employee is in charge of updating the informtion of the employees in the company.&lt;br&gt;Supplier, registers all the suppliers of the IMS.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Product has a record of all the proudcts that are in the system, linked to their category.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Category registers all the groups in which products can be classified.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sales shows the sales that has been already processed by the Billing view.&lt;br&gt;Billing, registers all the bills showing the stock, the total price, and the Customer details&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The previous version of the system is open for changes related to refactor code, functionality on logout buttons and a login service.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="320" width="930" x="90" y="4270" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
